1
00:01:36,129 --> 00:01:37,430
Cardiology outpatient clinic,

2
00:01:37,564 --> 00:01:39,032
number 14, You Xiaoli,

3
00:01:39,332 --> 00:01:41,534
please proceed to Room 2.

4
00:01:43,603 --> 00:01:44,604
Hello, Dr. Ye.

5
00:01:44,971 --> 00:01:45,371
Hello.

6
00:01:50,877 --> 00:01:52,145
You Xiaoli, right?

7
00:01:54,247 --> 00:01:55,315
What's your current condition?

8
00:01:55,882 --> 00:01:57,183
A 1.5-centimeter ventricular septal defect.

9
00:01:57,317 --> 00:01:58,485
Currently with pulmonary hypertension

10
00:01:58,518 --> 00:01:59,252
and bidirectional shunting.

11
00:02:03,356 --> 00:02:04,791
When was the pulmonary hypertension discovered?

12
00:02:05,425 --> 00:02:07,327
When I had an echocardiogram as a child

13
00:02:07,527 --> 00:02:08,828
and they found this condition,

14
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:10,997
my pulmonary artery pressure was already quite high.

15
00:02:11,764 --> 00:02:13,766
My family didn't take it too seriously.

16
00:02:15,368 --> 00:02:16,236
Let me listen first.

17
00:02:16,469 --> 00:02:16,836
Okay.

18
00:02:36,256 --> 00:02:37,724
Later, when I was twenty-seven or twenty-eight

19
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:38,758
and became pregnant,

20
00:02:39,292 --> 00:02:40,126
my pulmonary artery pressure

21
00:02:40,126 --> 00:02:41,294
rose even further.

22
00:02:41,895 --> 00:02:43,730
Over the years, whenever I exert myself,

23
00:02:44,063 --> 00:02:45,265
the chest tightness and shortness of breath

24
00:02:45,265 --> 00:02:46,533
have become more and more obvious.

25
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:48,635
I've been taking medication all along.

26
00:02:48,935 --> 00:02:51,170
You've been using targeted pulmonary vasodilators?

27
00:02:51,437 --> 00:02:51,804
Yes.

28
00:02:52,405 --> 00:02:54,307
This new drug has worked pretty well.

29
00:02:55,675 --> 00:02:57,243
My previous doctor said

30
00:02:57,544 --> 00:02:58,344
I might

31
00:02:58,711 --> 00:03:00,313
have a chance at surgery now.

32
00:03:01,314 --> 00:03:03,116
Strictly speaking, in your current condition,

33
00:03:04,183 --> 00:03:05,385
there is no indication for surgery.

34
00:03:06,953 --> 00:03:07,954
I heard

35
00:03:08,087 --> 00:03:10,123
Dongli Hospital's Heart Center

36
00:03:10,323 --> 00:03:11,224
is excellent,

37
00:03:11,925 --> 00:03:12,825
and has performed many operations

38
00:03:12,825 --> 00:03:14,027
other hospitals couldn't do.

39
00:03:14,561 --> 00:03:16,629
That's why I came specifically to see you.

40
00:03:20,266 --> 00:03:21,034
Please wait a moment.

41
00:03:24,971 --> 00:03:25,238
Hello?

42
00:03:25,705 --> 00:03:26,272
Hello, Director.

43
00:03:26,773 --> 00:03:27,307
I have

44
00:03:27,373 --> 00:03:28,441
a patient with pulmonary hypertension.

45
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:29,976
Her case is unusual.

46
00:03:30,109 --> 00:03:31,077
A 1.5-centimeter VSD,

47
00:03:31,144 --> 00:03:32,045
with bidirectional shunting.

48
00:03:32,512 --> 00:03:34,247
She strongly wants surgery.

49
00:03:34,614 --> 00:03:35,815
Could you come take a look?

50
00:03:35,815 --> 00:03:36,282
Right now?

51
00:03:36,883 --> 00:03:38,084
Okay. I'm coming.

52
00:03:38,685 --> 00:03:39,452
Ask Director Lin too.

53
00:03:39,586 --> 00:03:40,653
Have him come over if he's free.

54
00:03:40,887 --> 00:03:41,754
Okay, no problem.

55
00:03:41,854 --> 00:03:42,488
Thank you, Director.

56
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:51,030
Hello?

57
00:03:51,197 --> 00:03:51,931
Hello, Director Lin.

58
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:53,166
We admitted a patient with a large VSD,

59
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:54,767
pulmonary hypertension, and bidirectional shunting.

60
00:03:55,201 --> 00:03:55,835
Director Zhou asked

61
00:03:55,835 --> 00:03:56,603
if you could come take a look.

62
00:03:56,703 --> 00:03:57,804
Okay. I'm on my way.

63
00:03:58,504 --> 00:03:58,905
I'll leave it to you.

64
00:03:59,105 --> 00:03:59,372
Okay.

65
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:06,079
Dr. Xiaoran,

66
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:07,547
didn't you already report

67
00:04:07,547 --> 00:04:08,114
to Critical Care?

68
00:04:08,114 --> 00:04:09,082
Why are you here?

69
00:04:09,115 --> 00:04:09,949
Beds 5 and 10

70
00:04:10,016 --> 00:04:11,150
were a little unstable last night.

71
00:04:11,284 --> 00:04:12,318
I came back to check on them.

72
00:04:14,354 --> 00:04:15,755
They're stable now.

73
00:04:15,922 --> 00:04:16,789
Don't worry.

74
00:04:17,156 --> 00:04:18,191
Director Lin came by

75
00:04:18,224 --> 00:04:19,225
to examine them early this morning.

76
00:04:19,392 --> 00:04:19,926
He just left.

77
00:04:22,528 --> 00:04:23,596
Right, Xiao Du. Come here.

78
00:04:25,198 --> 00:04:26,532
This patient has diabetes,

79
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:28,034
so the wound

80
00:04:28,034 --> 00:04:28,768
will heal more slowly.

81
00:04:28,968 --> 00:04:30,637
Check and palpate the lower limb often.

82
00:04:31,638 --> 00:04:32,805
Director Lin told me too.

83
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:35,008
He also said

84
00:04:35,274 --> 00:04:36,009
that during this period,

85
00:04:36,075 --> 00:04:36,709
if anything comes up

86
00:04:36,709 --> 00:04:37,844
on our side,

87
00:04:38,244 --> 00:04:39,145
we should tell him immediately.

88
00:04:39,412 --> 00:04:40,313
He'll handle it.

89
00:04:43,316 --> 00:04:43,783
Xiaoran,

90
00:04:44,150 --> 00:04:45,084
although none of us

91
00:04:45,084 --> 00:04:45,918
wants to see you go,

92
00:04:46,452 --> 00:04:47,053
still,

93
00:04:47,687 --> 00:04:48,688
go do your best without worrying.

94
00:05:02,468 --> 00:05:03,636
You've only taken this medicine for three months,

95
00:05:04,904 --> 00:05:05,805
just three months,

96
00:05:06,005 --> 00:05:07,006
and both the tricuspid regurgitation

97
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,007
and pulmonary regurgitation

98
00:05:08,007 --> 00:05:08,908
have already improved.

99
00:05:10,109 --> 00:05:10,543
Director,

100
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:12,045
can I have surgery?

101
00:05:12,812 --> 00:05:14,147
My previous doctor said

102
00:05:14,347 --> 00:05:16,049
both Cardiology and Cardiac Surgery

103
00:05:16,549 --> 00:05:18,251
had ways to treat my VSD.

104
00:05:21,854 --> 00:05:22,588
How old are you this year?

105
00:05:22,922 --> 00:05:23,623
Seventeen.

106
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:24,824
I'll be an adult next year.

107
00:05:26,225 --> 00:05:27,427
It's okay, Director Lin.

108
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:28,561
For my mother's condition,

109
00:05:28,594 --> 00:05:29,962
I've always accompanied her to appointments.

110
00:05:30,196 --> 00:05:31,531
I know her condition very well.

111
00:05:31,764 --> 00:05:32,932
You can tell me anything.

112
00:05:36,202 --> 00:05:36,569
All right.

113
00:05:38,771 --> 00:05:39,105
I

114
00:05:40,273 --> 00:05:41,107
don't recommend surgery.

115
00:05:44,410 --> 00:05:45,078
Since

116
00:05:45,111 --> 00:05:46,245
the targeted medication is working,

117
00:05:47,046 --> 00:05:48,247
you can continue conservative treatment.

118
00:05:52,085 --> 00:05:54,053
My previous doctor told me

119
00:05:54,554 --> 00:05:56,122
surgery was possible.

120
00:05:56,422 --> 00:05:57,757
They could close my VSD

121
00:05:58,157 --> 00:05:58,991
or patch it.

122
00:05:59,358 --> 00:06:00,593
Your pulmonary artery pressure is very high.

123
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:01,928
Considering your blood gas results

124
00:06:01,961 --> 00:06:02,762
and the clinical finding

125
00:06:02,795 --> 00:06:04,063
of cyanotic lips,

126
00:06:04,397 --> 00:06:05,732
the surgical risk is very high

127
00:06:06,432 --> 00:06:07,400
and the potential benefit is very small.

128
00:06:08,468 --> 00:06:09,635
So I don't recommend surgery.

129
00:06:10,136 --> 00:06:11,804
I came all the way to your hospital

130
00:06:12,472 --> 00:06:13,806
because I wanted surgery.

131
00:06:17,810 --> 00:06:19,011
Have you had cardiac catheterization?

132
00:06:19,445 --> 00:06:20,046
Not yet.

133
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:21,047
How about this?

134
00:06:21,314 --> 00:06:22,515
We'll admit you first

135
00:06:22,882 --> 00:06:23,950
and arrange some tests.

136
00:06:24,083 --> 00:06:25,585
We'll make a decision after a thorough evaluation.

137
00:06:25,718 --> 00:06:26,119
Okay?

138
00:06:26,786 --> 00:06:27,253
Okay.

139
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:28,588
Write the admission order.

140
00:06:28,888 --> 00:06:29,255
Okay.

141
00:06:29,288 --> 00:06:30,823
Mom, see? What did I tell you?

142
00:06:30,990 --> 00:06:32,425
Don't underestimate young doctors.

143
00:06:32,625 --> 00:06:33,359
Young doctors

144
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:34,527
can still summon the real experts, right?

145
00:06:34,894 --> 00:06:36,262
And she summoned two at once.

146
00:06:41,801 --> 00:06:43,302
Coordinate with the cath lab.

147
00:06:43,770 --> 00:06:45,004
You Xiaoli's cardiac catheterization—

148
00:06:45,004 --> 00:06:45,705
expedite it if possible.

149
00:06:46,205 --> 00:06:46,672
Okay.

150
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:48,374
Director,

151
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:50,643
in You Xiaoli's current condition,

152
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:51,844
does that mean neither medication

153
00:06:51,878 --> 00:06:52,812
nor surgery

154
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:53,913
can fully solve

155
00:06:53,913 --> 00:06:54,647
her problem?

156
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:55,481
Yes.

157
00:06:56,516 --> 00:06:57,383
And her condition

158
00:06:57,450 --> 00:06:58,451
will only keep worsening.

159
00:06:59,352 --> 00:07:00,753
She's only forty-five,

160
00:07:01,354 --> 00:07:02,288
but her VSD

161
00:07:02,321 --> 00:07:03,156
could have been treated

162
00:07:03,189 --> 00:07:04,757
in a timely manner years ago.

163
00:07:05,191 --> 00:07:06,325
How did it end up

164
00:07:06,325 --> 00:07:07,593
progressing this far?

165
00:07:08,761 --> 00:07:09,195
Everyone

166
00:07:09,195 --> 00:07:10,463
has their own difficulties.

167
00:07:11,063 --> 00:07:11,764
Maybe when she was young,

168
00:07:11,764 --> 00:07:12,832
her family couldn't afford treatment,

169
00:07:13,332 --> 00:07:14,233
or they lacked

170
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:15,067
the necessary medical awareness.

171
00:07:15,334 --> 00:07:16,602
That's how it was delayed until now.

172
00:07:17,970 --> 00:07:18,704
What a shame.

173
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:20,873
Ask

174
00:07:20,873 --> 00:07:22,008
Director Duan from Thoracic Surgery

175
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:22,909
to join the consultation too.

176
00:07:23,242 --> 00:07:23,609
Okay.

177
00:07:27,079 --> 00:07:28,881
But the results show your pulmonary vascular resistance

178
00:07:29,015 --> 00:07:30,016
is at the borderline

179
00:07:30,349 --> 00:07:31,317
and you're not suitable for surgery.

180
00:07:32,552 --> 00:07:33,586
Whether it's VSD closure

181
00:07:33,653 --> 00:07:34,454
or surgical repair,

182
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:36,055
we don't recommend either.

183
00:07:36,923 --> 00:07:37,957
If you have surgery,

184
00:07:38,224 --> 00:07:39,492
your condition could very likely

185
00:07:39,692 --> 00:07:40,626
become worse than it is now.

186
00:07:43,796 --> 00:07:45,965
I agree with Director Zhou.

187
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:47,967
I understand.

188
00:07:48,401 --> 00:07:50,603
But since the targeted medication is working now,

189
00:07:51,037 --> 00:07:52,638
shouldn't I seize

190
00:07:52,705 --> 00:07:54,640
this rare window for surgery?

191
00:07:55,107 --> 00:07:56,242
Judging from

192
00:07:56,576 --> 00:07:58,344
the current degree of pulmonary vascular remodeling,

193
00:07:58,878 --> 00:07:59,812
the benefit of surgery

194
00:08:01,113 --> 00:08:01,747
is uncertain.

195
00:08:01,948 --> 00:08:02,915
And you'd be facing

196
00:08:03,049 --> 00:08:04,050
enormous risk,

197
00:08:04,283 --> 00:08:05,485
trauma, and expense.

198
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:07,119
But

199
00:08:07,954 --> 00:08:09,322
if I don't at least try,

200
00:08:10,089 --> 00:08:11,524
I won't be able to accept it.

201
00:08:17,029 --> 00:08:18,264
Let's say this is your heart.

202
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:21,868
There's a defect here.

203
00:08:22,235 --> 00:08:23,035
Normally,

204
00:08:23,069 --> 00:08:24,103
we would patch the hole,

205
00:08:24,437 --> 00:08:25,238
and then the pulmonary artery pressure

206
00:08:25,238 --> 00:08:25,972
would come down.

207
00:08:26,806 --> 00:08:28,074
But your case is special.

208
00:08:28,441 --> 00:08:29,242
If we simply

209
00:08:29,275 --> 00:08:30,376
close this defect,

210
00:08:30,743 --> 00:08:31,310
the blood flowing

211
00:08:31,410 --> 00:08:32,545
from the left ventricle to the right

212
00:08:32,645 --> 00:08:33,212
would stop,

213
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:34,313
but the pathway allowing blood

214
00:08:34,313 --> 00:08:35,514
from the right ventricle to the left

215
00:08:35,615 --> 00:08:36,449
would also be closed.

216
00:08:36,849 --> 00:08:37,984
The blood in the right ventricle

217
00:08:37,984 --> 00:08:39,452
would then have nowhere to go but the pulmonary artery.

218
00:08:39,785 --> 00:08:41,854
If your pulmonary hypertension is irreversible,

219
00:08:41,888 --> 00:08:43,523
that could cause acute right heart failure,

220
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:45,224
with very serious consequences.

221
00:08:51,430 --> 00:08:52,965
I understand how you feel.

222
00:08:53,799 --> 00:08:55,368
But every medical decision

223
00:08:55,668 --> 00:08:56,469
requires us to weigh

224
00:08:56,569 --> 00:08:57,703
the benefits against the cost.

225
00:08:58,204 --> 00:08:59,705
If there is clear benefit at little cost,

226
00:08:59,872 --> 00:09:00,840
then of course we should proceed.

227
00:09:01,073 --> 00:09:02,241
But in your case,

228
00:09:02,642 --> 00:09:03,643
the evidence of benefit is insufficient

229
00:09:04,043 --> 00:09:05,077
and the cost is extremely high.

230
00:09:05,945 --> 00:09:06,746
So why force it?

231
00:09:08,681 --> 00:09:09,782
Continue the medication for now.

232
00:09:19,358 --> 00:09:19,725
Xiao Lin.

233
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:21,727
Director.

234
00:09:21,928 --> 00:09:22,795
Just finished surgery?

235
00:09:25,531 --> 00:09:26,365
I heard

236
00:09:26,432 --> 00:09:27,967
there's a patient with pulmonary hypertension

237
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:29,735
who strongly wants surgery,

238
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:31,704
but you refused

239
00:09:32,305 --> 00:09:33,806
to repair her VSD.

240
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:36,075
Cardiology performed

241
00:09:36,108 --> 00:09:37,209
cardiac catheterization

242
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:38,511
and found her pulmonary vascular resistance

243
00:09:38,544 --> 00:09:39,612
is already at the borderline.

244
00:09:40,212 --> 00:09:41,547
If we repair it now,

245
00:09:41,647 --> 00:09:42,548
there isn't enough evidence of benefit.

246
00:09:44,116 --> 00:09:45,785
What a shame. She's only in her forties.

247
00:09:46,385 --> 00:09:46,852
Exactly.

248
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,754
So for now, we'll have her continue

249
00:09:48,788 --> 00:09:49,488
the targeted medication.

250
00:09:53,526 --> 00:09:54,160
Director Zhou,

251
00:09:54,527 --> 00:09:56,395
you all want me to keep taking medication.

252
00:09:56,829 --> 00:09:58,397
In my current condition,

253
00:09:59,799 --> 00:10:01,534
can I last another year?

254
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:05,605
I honestly can't guarantee that.

255
00:10:14,413 --> 00:10:15,014
I understand.

256
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:18,918
I had a fellow patient before.

257
00:10:19,919 --> 00:10:21,153
She had been doing fine,

258
00:10:21,487 --> 00:10:24,724
then suddenly deteriorated off a cliff.

259
00:10:26,759 --> 00:10:28,194
She was gone within months.

260
00:10:28,928 --> 00:10:29,795
Director Zhou,

261
00:10:30,596 --> 00:10:32,231
could you help me?

262
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:34,133
As long as I can live one more year,

263
00:10:34,867 --> 00:10:36,369
even just one year.

264
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:39,305
So the reason you're insisting

265
00:10:39,372 --> 00:10:40,239
on surgery

266
00:10:41,707 --> 00:10:43,242
is to gain one more year?

267
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:45,277
Why?

268
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:49,715
It's a promise I made to my daughter.

269
00:10:57,923 --> 00:10:58,624
You don't have to

270
00:10:58,724 --> 00:10:59,425
be so pessimistic.

271
00:11:00,292 --> 00:11:01,160
Take your medicine on time,

272
00:11:01,594 --> 00:11:02,828
keep the disease under control,

273
00:11:03,262 --> 00:11:04,630
and maintain a positive mindset.

274
00:11:05,398 --> 00:11:05,965
Another year

275
00:11:06,766 --> 00:11:07,833
isn't impossible.

276
00:11:13,272 --> 00:11:14,306
Thank you, Director Zhou.

277
00:11:17,410 --> 00:11:18,110
Where is your daughter?

278
00:11:19,712 --> 00:11:20,713
She went to deliver some books.

279
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,448
I hope you'll like them.

280
00:11:22,848 --> 00:11:24,316
Your mother is a writer?

281
00:11:25,117 --> 00:11:26,686
My mom writes children's books.

282
00:11:27,453 --> 00:11:28,654
I know this book.

283
00:11:28,754 --> 00:11:30,022
I saw it in a bookstore a few days ago.

284
00:11:30,156 --> 00:11:31,390
It was on the bestseller list.

285
00:11:31,724 --> 00:11:32,491
Really?

286
00:11:33,526 --> 00:11:35,561
For my precious daughter, Linlang.

287
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:36,929
This is a gift

288
00:11:36,929 --> 00:11:37,930
from your mother.

289
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:38,431
Yes.

290
00:11:38,764 --> 00:11:39,632
When I was little,

291
00:11:39,832 --> 00:11:40,866
my mom told me

292
00:11:40,866 --> 00:11:41,867
bedtime stories every night.

293
00:11:41,934 --> 00:11:43,469
The Little Mermaid,

294
00:11:43,469 --> 00:11:44,370
Snow White,

295
00:11:44,403 --> 00:11:45,438
Black Cat Detective, Calabash Brothers...

296
00:11:45,471 --> 00:11:46,272
I got tired of all of them.

297
00:11:46,772 --> 00:11:47,873
So she'd make up stories on the spot.

298
00:11:48,174 --> 00:11:48,841
The stories she made up

299
00:11:48,874 --> 00:11:49,709
were my favorites.

300
00:11:49,842 --> 00:11:50,509
So she simply wrote all of them

301
00:11:50,509 --> 00:11:51,210
down.

302
00:11:51,944 --> 00:11:52,878
That's so loving.

303
00:11:52,945 --> 00:11:54,013
Yes. It's wonderful.

304
00:11:55,081 --> 00:11:56,282
Then... I'll get going.

305
00:11:56,549 --> 00:11:57,483
Thank you, and thank your mother.

306
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:58,784
We'll read them carefully.

307
00:11:59,985 --> 00:12:00,653
Thank you.

308
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:01,087
Thank you.

309
00:12:02,688 --> 00:12:04,190
Those two are really close.

310
00:12:05,091 --> 00:12:06,625
You Xiaoli is so seriously ill,

311
00:12:07,093 --> 00:12:07,960
and these past few days,

312
00:12:07,993 --> 00:12:08,828
it's only been that young girl

313
00:12:08,928 --> 00:12:09,595
looking after her.

314
00:12:09,962 --> 00:12:11,030
It doesn't seem like

315
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:12,431
there are any other family members.

316
00:12:13,466 --> 00:12:14,166
What does she have?

317
00:12:14,867 --> 00:12:15,935
Pulmonary hypertension.

318
00:12:16,602 --> 00:12:17,837
And it's already severe.

319
00:12:18,304 --> 00:12:19,238
Imagine

320
00:12:19,438 --> 00:12:21,006
if something happens to her mother...

321
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:23,709
what will that girl do?

322
00:12:41,961 --> 00:12:42,628
Xiaoli.

323
00:12:43,662 --> 00:12:44,530
My Xiaoli!

324
00:12:44,530 --> 00:12:44,964
Mom.

325
00:12:45,397 --> 00:12:45,831
Xiaoli.

326
00:12:45,831 --> 00:12:46,932
Why are you here?

327
00:12:47,066 --> 00:12:49,001
The moment I heard you needed major surgery,

328
00:12:49,735 --> 00:12:50,603
my vertigo

329
00:12:50,636 --> 00:12:51,904
flared up from the fright.

330
00:12:52,071 --> 00:12:53,439
I haven't slept

331
00:12:53,506 --> 00:12:54,974
a wink all night.

332
00:12:55,174 --> 00:12:56,375
I can't even eat.

333
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:57,476
And it rained two days ago,

334
00:12:57,676 --> 00:12:59,879
so my old arthritic leg hurts badly again.

335
00:13:00,246 --> 00:13:02,681
I was counting on my daughter to care for me.

336
00:13:02,848 --> 00:13:05,885
What a miserable life!

337
00:13:06,051 --> 00:13:09,455
My life is so bitter!

338
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:12,224
Grandma.

339
00:13:13,592 --> 00:13:14,927
Linlang.

340
00:13:15,561 --> 00:13:16,495
Family member,

341
00:13:16,929 --> 00:13:17,463
please keep your voice down.

342
00:13:17,530 --> 00:13:18,531
There are other patients here.

343
00:13:20,065 --> 00:13:20,566
Mom.

344
00:13:20,566 --> 00:13:22,268
Grandma's life is so hard.

345
00:13:22,535 --> 00:13:23,769
Let go of Linlang.

346
00:13:24,370 --> 00:13:25,271
Let her go.

347
00:13:25,838 --> 00:13:26,605
Linlang,

348
00:13:26,872 --> 00:13:28,474
go to the convenience store downstairs

349
00:13:28,974 --> 00:13:30,943
and buy some wet wipes for hands and mouth.

350
00:13:31,310 --> 00:13:33,012
And get Grandma

351
00:13:33,345 --> 00:13:34,547
some heat patches for her knees.

352
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:35,281
Okay.

353
00:13:36,015 --> 00:13:36,482
Go on.

354
00:13:39,451 --> 00:13:41,320
My life is so miserable.

355
00:13:43,289 --> 00:13:44,223
Miss Nurse,

356
00:13:44,757 --> 00:13:46,292
I'm going downstairs to buy something.

357
00:13:46,592 --> 00:13:48,027
My grandma is inside right now.

358
00:13:48,294 --> 00:13:48,994
If anything happens

359
00:13:48,994 --> 00:13:49,562
to my mother,

360
00:13:49,562 --> 00:13:50,563
call me anytime.

361
00:13:50,563 --> 00:13:51,063
I won't go far.

362
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:52,631
Okay. Don't worry.

363
00:13:53,032 --> 00:13:53,432
Thank you.

364
00:13:57,069 --> 00:13:58,237
You saw that just now, right?

365
00:13:58,437 --> 00:13:59,572
You Xiaoli is so sick,

366
00:14:00,105 --> 00:14:01,807
but from the moment her mother walked in,

367
00:14:02,107 --> 00:14:03,442
she didn't say a single caring

368
00:14:03,442 --> 00:14:04,043
or comforting word.

369
00:14:04,443 --> 00:14:05,911
Every tear was about her own suffering.

370
00:14:06,679 --> 00:14:08,080
Isn't that just making the patient feel worse?

371
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:09,215
You made money writing books,

372
00:14:09,715 --> 00:14:11,283
didn't you?

373
00:14:11,750 --> 00:14:12,985
Why did you sell your home?

374
00:14:13,953 --> 00:14:15,354
I'm seriously ill.

375
00:14:15,955 --> 00:14:17,089
I need lifelong medication,

376
00:14:17,456 --> 00:14:19,892
and I'm planning to have surgery.

377
00:14:20,159 --> 00:14:21,427
My savings aren't enough.

378
00:14:22,361 --> 00:14:23,262
How much did you sell it for?

379
00:14:24,797 --> 00:14:25,865
It must've been several million.

380
00:14:31,971 --> 00:14:32,771
No matter what,

381
00:14:33,572 --> 00:14:34,006
there's still Linlang,

382
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:35,674
your father and me,

383
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:37,042
and your sister and brother-in-law.

384
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:38,477
If anything really

385
00:14:38,744 --> 00:14:39,812
happens to you,

386
00:14:40,079 --> 00:14:41,146
leave the money with me.

387
00:14:41,447 --> 00:14:41,880
Linlang

388
00:14:42,414 --> 00:14:43,315
can be raised by your sister.

389
00:14:43,949 --> 00:14:45,517
It's just one more pair of chopsticks.

390
00:14:45,918 --> 00:14:46,986
Raising a child

391
00:14:48,287 --> 00:14:49,922
isn't just adding another pair of chopsticks.

392
00:14:50,189 --> 00:14:50,956
Besides,

393
00:14:51,957 --> 00:14:53,492
what gives you the right to decide for my sister?

394
00:14:54,827 --> 00:14:56,295
She's our own family's child.

395
00:14:56,595 --> 00:14:58,197
We wouldn't mistreat her.

396
00:15:00,332 --> 00:15:01,767
You wouldn't treat her well either.

397
00:15:02,635 --> 00:15:03,736
What do you mean by that?

398
00:15:05,271 --> 00:15:07,506
Your father and I raised you for twenty-three years,

399
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:09,074
all the way through college.

400
00:15:09,308 --> 00:15:10,309
Did we ever let you go hungry

401
00:15:10,542 --> 00:15:11,510
or freeze?

402
00:15:11,710 --> 00:15:12,745
How was that mistreating you?

403
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:15,147
My illness—

404
00:15:16,415 --> 00:15:18,183
if you'd taken it even a little seriously back then,

405
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:19,251
it never would've progressed

406
00:15:19,285 --> 00:15:20,452
to this point.

407
00:15:25,557 --> 00:15:26,926
We didn't understand.

408
00:15:27,626 --> 00:15:28,360
We thought

409
00:15:28,794 --> 00:15:30,396
you were just being a spoiled little girl.

410
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,368
I wanted to study the humanities,

411
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:39,271
but you forced me into science.

412
00:15:40,039 --> 00:15:41,206
You made me major in accounting

413
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:42,608
because you wanted me

414
00:15:42,708 --> 00:15:44,009
to work at your supermarket after graduation.

415
00:15:44,677 --> 00:15:46,045
My sister had excellent grades.

416
00:15:46,312 --> 00:15:48,013
She could've studied engineering

417
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,081
at a top university.

418
00:15:50,983 --> 00:15:52,551
But you secretly changed her application

419
00:15:52,551 --> 00:15:53,686
to preschool education.

420
00:15:53,852 --> 00:15:55,254
What's wrong with preschool education?

421
00:15:55,754 --> 00:15:56,989
She'd know how to raise children.

422
00:15:57,556 --> 00:15:59,124
What in-laws wouldn't like that?

423
00:15:59,925 --> 00:16:00,626
Exactly.

424
00:16:01,927 --> 00:16:03,095
You're always right.

425
00:16:04,463 --> 00:16:05,764
I don't want to argue with you.

426
00:16:07,266 --> 00:16:08,434
You came a long way.

427
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:09,568
You must be tired.

428
00:16:10,002 --> 00:16:11,003
Go home early.

429
00:16:14,707 --> 00:16:16,008
I have nothing else to say to you.

430
00:16:16,508 --> 00:16:17,443
I'll wait for Linlang to come back.

431
00:16:18,043 --> 00:16:19,511
I'll explain things directly to her.

432
00:16:22,014 --> 00:16:23,048
You don't need to wait.

433
00:16:24,483 --> 00:16:25,884
Everything was my decision.

434
00:16:27,186 --> 00:16:28,354
You are not allowed to bother her.

435
00:16:31,890 --> 00:16:33,225
I'm her grandmother.

436
00:16:33,726 --> 00:16:34,493
Do I not even have

437
00:16:34,526 --> 00:16:35,828
the right to talk to the child?

438
00:16:36,128 --> 00:16:37,496
You're far too overbearing.

439
00:16:38,397 --> 00:16:39,231
Now you remember

440
00:16:39,264 --> 00:16:40,566
you're her grandmother?

441
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:43,736
Since the day she was born,

442
00:16:44,570 --> 00:16:45,838
have you ever held her once,

443
00:16:46,605 --> 00:16:48,240
or changed a single diaper?

444
00:16:48,607 --> 00:16:50,542
Have you bought her one piece of clothing,

445
00:16:50,809 --> 00:16:51,944
or even one piece of candy?

446
00:16:52,511 --> 00:16:53,312
In your hearts,

447
00:16:53,412 --> 00:16:55,014
you've only ever cared about yourselves.

448
00:16:55,114 --> 00:16:56,648
Now you're settling accounts with me?

449
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:59,585
You made so much money from your books,

450
00:16:59,718 --> 00:17:00,386
and yet your father and I

451
00:17:00,586 --> 00:17:02,187
hardly enjoyed any benefit from you.

452
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:04,423
I'm sorry.

453
00:17:04,957 --> 00:17:06,191
I've disappointed you.

454
00:17:06,759 --> 00:17:07,960
My abilities are limited.

455
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:10,562
I can only look after myself and Linlang.

456
00:17:10,763 --> 00:17:11,764
We can look after Linlang.

457
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:13,132
We've already planned it all.

458
00:17:13,832 --> 00:17:14,833
She does reasonably well in school.

459
00:17:15,634 --> 00:17:17,302
She can study nursing in college

460
00:17:17,603 --> 00:17:18,971
and become a nurse.

461
00:17:19,505 --> 00:17:21,173
Look at your health now.

462
00:17:21,173 --> 00:17:21,573
You...

463
00:17:21,774 --> 00:17:22,875
and your father and I are getting older.

464
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:23,175
Mom.

465
00:17:23,642 --> 00:17:24,209
If we have

466
00:17:24,209 --> 00:17:25,344
a nurse in the family in the future,

467
00:17:25,811 --> 00:17:26,845
wouldn't that be useful?

468
00:17:27,112 --> 00:17:27,513
What's wrong?

469
00:17:27,746 --> 00:17:28,647
Are you having trouble breathing?

470
00:17:29,014 --> 00:17:29,515
Do you feel unwell?

471
00:17:32,284 --> 00:17:32,918
What's happening?

472
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:34,253
How did she suddenly get like this?

473
00:17:34,486 --> 00:17:34,853
Doctor!

474
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:36,088
Doctor, hurry!

475
00:17:36,188 --> 00:17:36,989
Family, step back.

476
00:17:39,391 --> 00:17:40,359
The patient is unstable.

477
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:41,527
Watch what you say around her.

478
00:17:42,795 --> 00:17:44,029
I didn't do anything to her.

479
00:17:44,763 --> 00:17:46,398
You Xiaoli had a pulmonary hypertensive crisis today.

480
00:17:46,665 --> 00:17:48,200
She stabilized for now after resuscitation.

481
00:17:49,067 --> 00:17:49,868
But her condition

482
00:17:49,868 --> 00:17:50,769
is still very poor.

483
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:53,072
What's her oxygen saturation now?

484
00:17:53,705 --> 00:17:54,506
Around 90.

485
00:17:57,743 --> 00:17:58,644
Keep her on strict bed rest

486
00:17:58,677 --> 00:17:59,611
for the next two days.

487
00:17:59,645 --> 00:18:00,446
Avoid any activity.

488
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:02,448
Keep her emotions as stable as possible.

489
00:18:03,048 --> 00:18:04,049
I'm sorry, Director.

490
00:18:04,850 --> 00:18:05,684
I originally thought

491
00:18:05,751 --> 00:18:06,752
that if she stayed in the ward,

492
00:18:06,919 --> 00:18:07,586
she could see

493
00:18:07,653 --> 00:18:08,387
her daughter every day

494
00:18:08,887 --> 00:18:10,189
and might feel better.

495
00:18:10,722 --> 00:18:11,824
But I didn't expect

496
00:18:12,157 --> 00:18:12,891
her mother...

497
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:13,725
I understand.

498
00:18:14,359 --> 00:18:15,160
This isn't your fault.

499
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:16,595
Let's observe her a little longer.

500
00:18:17,429 --> 00:18:18,997
If necessary, transfer her to the ICU.

501
00:18:19,565 --> 00:18:20,265
That would also shield her

502
00:18:20,265 --> 00:18:21,333
from unnecessary disturbances.

503
00:18:22,234 --> 00:18:22,601
Okay.

504
00:18:26,905 --> 00:18:27,372
Director Wei.

505
00:18:28,574 --> 00:18:29,508
All right. I'm coming now.

506
00:18:30,909 --> 00:18:31,610
And the baby?

507
00:18:31,610 --> 00:18:32,945
He has received standard treatment,

508
00:18:33,078 --> 00:18:33,879
and we've observed him

509
00:18:33,879 --> 00:18:35,080
for two weeks.

510
00:18:35,714 --> 00:18:36,748
But the diameter

511
00:18:36,782 --> 00:18:38,150
of his ductus arteriosus

512
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:39,184
hasn't decreased,

513
00:18:39,952 --> 00:18:41,453
and there is no sign of closure.

514
00:18:42,187 --> 00:18:42,688
Also,

515
00:18:42,688 --> 00:18:43,956
he still requires mechanical ventilation

516
00:18:43,956 --> 00:18:45,224
for respiratory support.

517
00:18:45,924 --> 00:18:46,825
His blood pressure

518
00:18:46,825 --> 00:18:48,427
still depends on medication.

519
00:18:50,362 --> 00:18:51,730
At present,

520
00:18:51,830 --> 00:18:53,031
his kidney function

521
00:18:53,065 --> 00:18:54,333
is mildly impaired.

522
00:18:54,867 --> 00:18:55,968
His creatinine is somewhat elevated,

523
00:18:56,268 --> 00:18:57,603
and his abdomen has started to distend.

524
00:18:57,836 --> 00:18:59,905
That suggests his intestinal function

525
00:19:00,239 --> 00:19:01,673
isn't very good either.

526
00:19:02,207 --> 00:19:03,041
Then

527
00:19:04,676 --> 00:19:06,645
how should we treat him next?

528
00:19:09,214 --> 00:19:10,315
The most important thing now

529
00:19:10,516 --> 00:19:11,283
is to find a way

530
00:19:11,283 --> 00:19:12,284
to close the ductus arteriosus.

531
00:19:12,518 --> 00:19:13,352
There are two options.

532
00:19:13,552 --> 00:19:14,987
One is surgical ligation.

533
00:19:15,587 --> 00:19:16,522
But the baby is too small.

534
00:19:17,189 --> 00:19:18,524
Open-chest surgery would be very traumatic.

535
00:19:19,091 --> 00:19:20,159
He may not tolerate it.

536
00:19:20,826 --> 00:19:21,293
The other option

537
00:19:21,293 --> 00:19:22,528
is a minimally invasive catheter intervention.

538
00:19:22,895 --> 00:19:23,795
Through a blood vessel in the leg,

539
00:19:23,962 --> 00:19:25,163
we would advance an occluder

540
00:19:25,264 --> 00:19:26,031
and close the opening.

541
00:19:27,165 --> 00:19:28,534
But the baby currently weighs

542
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:29,968
just over 800 grams.

543
00:19:30,502 --> 00:19:32,037
His vessels are extremely, extremely small.

544
00:19:32,604 --> 00:19:33,705
So the intervention

545
00:19:33,772 --> 00:19:34,406
would be very difficult.

546
00:19:35,107 --> 00:19:36,642
There are very few successful cases

547
00:19:37,309 --> 00:19:37,876
worldwide.

548
00:19:42,614 --> 00:19:44,149
If the opening is closed,

549
00:19:44,416 --> 00:19:45,250
will he be like

550
00:19:45,284 --> 00:19:46,752
other children in the future?

551
00:19:50,255 --> 00:19:51,490
If closure succeeds,

552
00:19:51,823 --> 00:19:53,325
the cardiac prognosis

553
00:19:53,492 --> 00:19:54,526
should be fairly good.

554
00:19:55,694 --> 00:19:56,328
But after all,

555
00:19:56,328 --> 00:19:57,496
he is an extremely premature infant.

556
00:19:58,130 --> 00:19:59,031
He may still face

557
00:19:59,064 --> 00:19:59,932
other challenges in the future.

558
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:06,972
These days in the incubator

559
00:20:08,407 --> 00:20:09,808
have already cost tens of thousands.

560
00:20:10,742 --> 00:20:12,344
And now another procedure...

561
00:20:13,345 --> 00:20:14,146
Director Zhou,

562
00:20:14,947 --> 00:20:16,348
will the operation

563
00:20:16,415 --> 00:20:17,516
cost tens of thousands more?

564
00:20:22,154 --> 00:20:22,955
What about social insurance?

565
00:20:23,922 --> 00:20:25,157
Have you enrolled the baby

566
00:20:25,190 --> 00:20:26,425
in newborn medical insurance?

567
00:20:27,726 --> 00:20:28,327
Don't cry.

568
00:20:28,694 --> 00:20:30,162
Our household registrations are back home.

569
00:20:30,796 --> 00:20:31,763
We can't enroll the baby

570
00:20:31,763 --> 00:20:32,664
in Dongjiang.

571
00:20:32,864 --> 00:20:33,765
We have to return home to do it.

572
00:20:34,166 --> 00:20:35,167
You can register for cross-region coverage,

573
00:20:35,467 --> 00:20:37,502
then settle the bill directly in Dongjiang.

574
00:20:37,869 --> 00:20:39,104
That way you won't have to pay first

575
00:20:39,171 --> 00:20:40,038
and claim reimbursement later.

576
00:20:40,672 --> 00:20:41,273
Also,

577
00:20:41,306 --> 00:20:43,108
did you know many places

578
00:20:43,175 --> 00:20:44,676
offer financial aid and subsidies

579
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:46,311
for extremely premature infants?

580
00:20:49,281 --> 00:20:51,216
How do we apply?

581
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:54,853
Leave that to me.

582
00:20:55,487 --> 00:20:56,455
I'll find out

583
00:20:56,521 --> 00:20:57,256
the exact procedure

584
00:20:57,556 --> 00:20:58,890
and help you get it done as soon as possible.

585
00:21:00,792 --> 00:21:02,361
Thank you, Sister Ouyang.

586
00:21:02,694 --> 00:21:03,362
Don't cry.

587
00:21:03,395 --> 00:21:04,363
If you really want to thank me,

588
00:21:04,563 --> 00:21:05,998
take good care of yourself first.

589
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:08,767
Have you named the baby?

590
00:21:09,001 --> 00:21:10,202
You'll need a name for the insurance application.

591
00:21:12,437 --> 00:21:13,438
While I was pregnant,

592
00:21:13,672 --> 00:21:15,007
we considered a few,

593
00:21:15,374 --> 00:21:16,808
but never decided.

594
00:21:17,809 --> 00:21:18,710
Thinking about it now,

595
00:21:20,345 --> 00:21:21,313
nothing matters more

596
00:21:21,613 --> 00:21:22,914
than health.

597
00:21:25,917 --> 00:21:28,754
How about Gong Youkang?

598
00:21:29,921 --> 00:21:30,889
"You" as in blessing,

599
00:21:31,757 --> 00:21:32,758
and "Kang" as in health.

600
00:21:34,526 --> 00:21:37,195
And his nickname can be Doudou.

601
00:21:40,065 --> 00:21:40,766
That's a good name.

602
00:21:41,933 --> 00:21:43,201
Wait for my update.

603
00:21:43,735 --> 00:21:44,569
I'm going to ask about it now.

604
00:21:46,071 --> 00:21:46,805
Take good care of her.

605
00:21:47,773 --> 00:21:48,407
Thank you.

606
00:21:49,207 --> 00:21:50,075
Thank you. Don't cry.

607
00:21:50,709 --> 00:21:51,476
Thank you. Thank you.

608
00:21:58,684 --> 00:22:00,786
Continue straight for one kilometer, then turn right.

609
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:02,721
Most of the time,

610
00:22:02,854 --> 00:22:04,289
we follow up at the Children's Hospital.

611
00:22:04,523 --> 00:22:06,158
Today we specifically booked

612
00:22:06,158 --> 00:22:07,426
an expert at Dongda University Children's Hospital.

613
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:09,161
It's good to hear from different doctors.

614
00:22:09,494 --> 00:22:10,996
Yes. Cross-checking

615
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:11,596
can't hurt.

616
00:22:12,731 --> 00:22:13,532
Uncle Zhou,

617
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:15,801
why did I get sick?

618
00:22:26,845 --> 00:22:27,879
Why did I just sneeze?

619
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:30,482
See?

620
00:22:30,682 --> 00:22:32,084
Uncle Zhou caught a cold too, right?

621
00:22:34,152 --> 00:22:34,686
Senlin,

622
00:22:35,153 --> 00:22:36,455
everyone gets sick.

623
00:22:37,122 --> 00:22:37,989
Being sick is normal.

624
00:22:38,290 --> 00:22:38,790
You're no different

625
00:22:38,824 --> 00:22:39,725
from anyone else.

626
00:22:40,926 --> 00:22:41,360
Also,

627
00:22:41,893 --> 00:22:42,961
what does Uncle Zhou do?

628
00:22:44,596 --> 00:22:45,931
He's a doctor.

629
00:22:46,231 --> 00:22:47,232
He treats illnesses.

630
00:22:47,466 --> 00:22:47,866
Exactly.

631
00:22:48,533 --> 00:22:49,801
So you don't need to be afraid when you're sick.

632
00:22:50,368 --> 00:22:51,436
Mom will protect you,

633
00:22:51,837 --> 00:22:52,871
and doctors will help you too.

634
00:22:53,705 --> 00:22:55,073
My mom said that too.

635
00:22:55,807 --> 00:22:57,175
She also said

636
00:22:57,476 --> 00:22:59,878
Uncle Zhou is an excellent doctor

637
00:23:00,278 --> 00:23:02,013
who's really good at treating people.

638
00:23:02,514 --> 00:23:02,881
That's right.

639
00:23:03,115 --> 00:23:04,449
And he's very handsome.

640
00:23:11,156 --> 00:23:12,290
Your mom has good taste.

641
00:23:14,359 --> 00:23:15,927
Why do Uncle Zhou's clothes

642
00:23:16,228 --> 00:23:17,562
smell so nice?

643
00:23:19,564 --> 00:23:21,133
Lane guidance activated.

644
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:22,033
Do they?

645
00:23:23,535 --> 00:23:25,003
It's the same scent

646
00:23:25,103 --> 00:23:26,304
as Mom's.

647
00:23:29,574 --> 00:23:30,876
Why are you so talkative today?

648
00:23:31,209 --> 00:23:32,244
Take a little rest.

649
00:23:38,850 --> 00:23:39,384
I put too much on.

650
00:23:44,356 --> 00:23:45,524
This one works well.

651
00:23:47,926 --> 00:23:48,326
Hello.

652
00:23:49,928 --> 00:23:50,328
Enjoy.

653
00:23:50,395 --> 00:23:50,796
Thank you.

654
00:23:51,463 --> 00:23:51,763
Senlin.

655
00:23:51,863 --> 00:23:53,231
This is the supreme pizza you ordered.

656
00:23:57,369 --> 00:23:57,836
Senlin.

657
00:23:57,969 --> 00:23:58,303
Isn't this

658
00:23:58,303 --> 00:23:59,704
your favorite restaurant?

659
00:23:59,805 --> 00:24:01,006
Eat a little more today, okay?

660
00:24:02,307 --> 00:24:03,074
Thank you.

661
00:24:04,543 --> 00:24:05,477
Mu Hongxia told me

662
00:24:05,610 --> 00:24:06,411
you were helping her arrange

663
00:24:06,411 --> 00:24:07,412
newborn medical insurance.

664
00:24:08,513 --> 00:24:09,514
I've already asked about it.

665
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:11,216
It isn't that complicated.

666
00:24:11,283 --> 00:24:12,484
It should be processed soon.

667
00:24:12,984 --> 00:24:13,952
They can settle the bill directly across regions.

668
00:24:15,287 --> 00:24:15,720
That's great.

669
00:24:16,321 --> 00:24:17,155
That'll ease

670
00:24:17,155 --> 00:24:18,123
a lot of their financial pressure.

671
00:24:18,690 --> 00:24:19,391
It's all thanks to you.

672
00:24:20,692 --> 00:24:21,393
It's just making a few calls

673
00:24:21,393 --> 00:24:22,594
and running a few errands.

674
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:23,395
I'm happy

675
00:24:23,395 --> 00:24:24,196
if I can help them.

676
00:24:26,765 --> 00:24:28,133
They've decided to proceed with surgery,

677
00:24:28,834 --> 00:24:29,801
so I also wanted to ask

678
00:24:30,268 --> 00:24:30,836
whether you have a product

679
00:24:30,836 --> 00:24:31,870
suitable for their baby.

680
00:24:32,437 --> 00:24:33,171
Actually, we do.

681
00:24:33,572 --> 00:24:34,706
But it's only indicated

682
00:24:35,006 --> 00:24:36,441
for a ductus arteriosus

683
00:24:36,875 --> 00:24:38,009
3.5 millimeters or smaller.

684
00:24:38,276 --> 00:24:39,244
What if it's larger than 3.5?

685
00:24:39,311 --> 00:24:40,745
It isn't absolutely impossible.

686
00:24:41,079 --> 00:24:41,880
I've also seen

687
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:42,614
a few isolated reports.

688
00:24:42,914 --> 00:24:43,748
But it would involve

689
00:24:43,782 --> 00:24:44,850
off-label use.

690
00:24:48,253 --> 00:24:49,120
I had been considering

691
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:50,322
asking my mother to help.

692
00:24:50,655 --> 00:24:52,190
She'll soon be back from Chengdu.

693
00:24:52,424 --> 00:24:53,692
Only she has enough experience

694
00:24:53,692 --> 00:24:55,126
and skill to complete this procedure.

695
00:24:56,728 --> 00:24:57,395
But if the product

696
00:24:57,395 --> 00:24:58,129
isn't indicated,

697
00:25:02,567 --> 00:25:03,768
I'll be frank:

698
00:25:04,169 --> 00:25:05,036
As for this matter,

699
00:25:05,403 --> 00:25:06,905
if it succeeds, of course that would be great.

700
00:25:07,172 --> 00:25:08,173
But if it fails,

701
00:25:08,507 --> 00:25:09,875
using a device off-label

702
00:25:10,075 --> 00:25:11,209
could invite criticism.

703
00:25:11,643 --> 00:25:12,677
Professor Fang

704
00:25:12,744 --> 00:25:13,745
would be falling into

705
00:25:13,812 --> 00:25:14,813
the same trap twice.

706
00:25:15,914 --> 00:25:16,448
Exactly.

707
00:25:17,415 --> 00:25:18,517
After what happened with Xuemei,

708
00:25:19,050 --> 00:25:19,718
I don't know whether Dongli

709
00:25:19,751 --> 00:25:21,052
would be willing to work with her again.

710
00:25:21,953 --> 00:25:22,320
Yes.

711
00:25:28,293 --> 00:25:30,896
We terminated our collaboration with Professor Fang.

712
00:25:31,630 --> 00:25:32,998
If we restart it now,

713
00:25:33,632 --> 00:25:35,267
less than a year later,

714
00:25:36,601 --> 00:25:37,369
would it

715
00:25:38,303 --> 00:25:39,104
raise objections

716
00:25:39,905 --> 00:25:41,172
from other colleagues?

717
00:25:42,073 --> 00:25:42,574
Of course,

718
00:25:43,408 --> 00:25:44,943
I'm not saying this

719
00:25:44,943 --> 00:25:45,810
from the hospital's standpoint.

720
00:25:45,844 --> 00:25:46,645
about this.

721
00:25:47,145 --> 00:25:48,446
An intervention this difficult

722
00:25:49,648 --> 00:25:50,949
would be

723
00:25:51,249 --> 00:25:52,517
a major challenge even for Dr. Fang.

724
00:25:53,351 --> 00:25:53,785
Yes.

725
00:25:54,886 --> 00:25:56,288
But during this period,

726
00:25:56,521 --> 00:25:57,722
Professor Fang has performed similar

727
00:25:57,756 --> 00:25:58,623
high-difficulty interventions elsewhere

728
00:25:59,024 --> 00:26:00,558
and accumulated more successful cases.

729
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:02,627
And as you know,

730
00:26:03,595 --> 00:26:04,029
if a hemodynamically significant

731
00:26:04,029 --> 00:26:04,496
patent ductus arteriosus

732
00:26:04,529 --> 00:26:05,664
is left untreated,

733
00:26:06,164 --> 00:26:07,566
the baby may die very soon.

734
00:26:13,004 --> 00:26:13,638
President Wang,

735
00:26:15,006 --> 00:26:15,974
you're a veteran.

736
00:26:16,675 --> 00:26:18,209
You've weathered many storms.

737
00:26:19,077 --> 00:26:20,111
You know very well

738
00:26:20,879 --> 00:26:22,347
that if either a hospital or a doctor,

739
00:26:23,281 --> 00:26:24,416
once bitten,

740
00:26:24,482 --> 00:26:25,850
shies away forever,

741
00:26:26,851 --> 00:26:27,652
patients will never

742
00:26:27,652 --> 00:26:28,653
see any hope.

743
00:26:35,694 --> 00:26:35,994
Here.

744
00:26:37,529 --> 00:26:38,163
Professor Fang already knows

745
00:26:38,196 --> 00:26:39,331
about little Doudou.

746
00:26:40,165 --> 00:26:40,565
Really?

747
00:26:41,366 --> 00:26:42,968
Someone posted about it on the congenital heart forum.

748
00:26:44,369 --> 00:26:45,203
There's no skim milk.

749
00:26:46,171 --> 00:26:46,705
That's okay.

750
00:26:48,206 --> 00:26:48,673
Right.

751
00:26:49,074 --> 00:26:49,841
He's been in the incubator

752
00:26:49,841 --> 00:26:50,809
for four weeks already.

753
00:26:51,176 --> 00:26:52,410
Medical treatment hasn't worked.

754
00:26:53,545 --> 00:26:55,246
This procedure is indeed very difficult.

755
00:26:55,413 --> 00:26:56,514
You're the only one who can do it.

756
00:26:58,650 --> 00:26:59,517
I'm willing.

757
00:27:00,986 --> 00:27:02,120
What do the parents want?

758
00:27:03,321 --> 00:27:04,022
I knew

759
00:27:04,289 --> 00:27:04,789
if I asked,

760
00:27:04,823 --> 00:27:05,690
you'd agree.

761
00:27:06,024 --> 00:27:07,158
The parents' wishes are very clear.

762
00:27:08,626 --> 00:27:09,527
Can you send me

763
00:27:09,594 --> 00:27:10,795
the patient's records?

764
00:27:22,073 --> 00:27:24,309
He really is

765
00:27:24,342 --> 00:27:24,709
a suitable candidate

766
00:27:24,709 --> 00:27:25,644
for transcatheter PDA closure.

767
00:27:26,411 --> 00:27:27,412
He's been alive four weeks

768
00:27:27,412 --> 00:27:28,646
and has gained only twenty grams.

769
00:27:29,681 --> 00:27:30,515
Without intervention,

770
00:27:30,515 --> 00:27:31,449
there's truly no hope.

771
00:27:32,517 --> 00:27:33,952
Let's assess him as soon as possible.

772
00:27:39,491 --> 00:27:41,493
Have you spoken with hospital leadership?

773
00:27:43,695 --> 00:27:44,529
We've discussed it with them.

774
00:27:46,931 --> 00:27:47,265
Mom,

775
00:27:48,133 --> 00:27:48,967
for this procedure,

776
00:27:49,768 --> 00:27:51,036
I want to operate with you

777
00:27:51,469 --> 00:27:52,237
as your assistant.

778
00:27:53,171 --> 00:27:54,205
That would be beneath your ability.

779
00:27:54,572 --> 00:27:55,807
How could I miss

780
00:27:56,174 --> 00:27:56,975
such a valuable learning opportunity?

781
00:27:57,642 --> 00:27:58,877
How about this?

782
00:27:59,844 --> 00:28:00,445
This time,

783
00:28:00,945 --> 00:28:02,714
I'll assist Professor Fang.

784
00:28:03,314 --> 00:28:04,549
That way, internally and externally,

785
00:28:05,083 --> 00:28:06,985
we can say I led the procedure.

786
00:28:07,952 --> 00:28:09,354
If anything happens,

787
00:28:10,555 --> 00:28:11,389
I'll take responsibility.

788
00:28:17,829 --> 00:28:19,130
And the device?

789
00:28:19,130 --> 00:28:19,631
No problem.

790
00:28:25,036 --> 00:28:25,670
You two...

791
00:28:26,071 --> 00:28:26,871
what's going on?

792
00:28:30,475 --> 00:28:31,676
You noticed that quickly?

793
00:28:32,243 --> 00:28:33,211
How could you hide it?

794
00:28:34,879 --> 00:28:35,914
When did this start?

795
00:28:36,614 --> 00:28:37,282
Not long ago.

796
00:28:38,116 --> 00:28:38,950
We planned to tell you

797
00:28:38,983 --> 00:28:39,851
in person when you came back.

798
00:28:40,351 --> 00:28:41,086
I'm back now.

799
00:28:41,553 --> 00:28:42,153
So tell me.

800
00:28:53,431 --> 00:28:54,666
But given your positions,

801
00:28:54,799 --> 00:28:57,035
will the hospital and company be okay with it?

802
00:29:03,641 --> 00:29:04,109
We'll deal with that.

803
00:29:05,910 --> 00:29:06,678
Don't worry.

804
00:29:07,011 --> 00:29:08,146
We'll be very clear

805
00:29:08,213 --> 00:29:09,047
about separating our personal lives

806
00:29:09,047 --> 00:29:09,948
from our work.

807
00:29:10,682 --> 00:29:11,649
I'm not worried.

808
00:29:11,783 --> 00:29:13,251
I actually find it rather amusing.

809
00:29:13,551 --> 00:29:14,385
The hopeless bachelor

810
00:29:14,452 --> 00:29:15,754
in our family

811
00:29:15,854 --> 00:29:17,255
wandered around for over a decade

812
00:29:17,322 --> 00:29:18,156
and still ended up with you.

813
00:29:19,891 --> 00:29:20,625
Hopeless?

814
00:29:22,127 --> 00:29:22,760
How hopeless?

815
00:29:24,162 --> 00:29:25,396
Come on, let's celebrate.

816
00:29:36,074 --> 00:29:37,275
I truly didn't expect

817
00:29:37,275 --> 00:29:39,711
the great Professor Fang to step in again.

818
00:29:41,045 --> 00:29:42,046
That kind of courage...

819
00:29:42,347 --> 00:29:43,481
I genuinely admire it.

820
00:29:44,048 --> 00:29:45,750
Professor Fang's procedure

821
00:29:45,850 --> 00:29:46,518
will still use

822
00:29:46,518 --> 00:29:47,952
a product supplied through our company.

823
00:29:49,354 --> 00:29:50,088
This product

824
00:29:50,121 --> 00:29:51,256
may be rather niche.

825
00:29:51,456 --> 00:29:52,090
I wonder whether you have

826
00:29:52,090 --> 00:29:52,924
the courage to take it on.

827
00:29:55,226 --> 00:29:56,561
Don't try to provoke me.

828
00:29:57,695 --> 00:29:58,763
We're open for business.

829
00:29:59,164 --> 00:30:00,665
We never turn customers away.

830
00:30:01,232 --> 00:30:02,267
Whatever product she wants,

831
00:30:02,600 --> 00:30:04,369
we'll find a way to supply it.

832
00:30:04,736 --> 00:30:05,069
Good.

833
00:30:05,403 --> 00:30:05,970
I'll send you

834
00:30:05,970 --> 00:30:06,905
the detailed information later.

835
00:30:07,038 --> 00:30:07,639
Also,

836
00:30:07,639 --> 00:30:09,007
I want to help little Doudou apply

837
00:30:09,073 --> 00:30:10,375
for financial assistance from a foundation.

838
00:30:10,608 --> 00:30:12,243
His family really is struggling.

839
00:30:12,477 --> 00:30:13,745
No problem. But

840
00:30:13,812 --> 00:30:14,679
there's a condition.

841
00:30:15,880 --> 00:30:16,514
I knew it.

842
00:30:17,315 --> 00:30:18,149
What condition?

843
00:30:24,122 --> 00:30:24,956
Wang Zhifeng called me

844
00:30:24,956 --> 00:30:25,757
a couple of days ago.

845
00:30:27,292 --> 00:30:27,692
Ouyang,

846
00:30:28,026 --> 00:30:29,160
I don't interfere

847
00:30:29,327 --> 00:30:30,428
in your private life.

848
00:30:31,162 --> 00:30:32,564
And if you're close to a department director,

849
00:30:32,931 --> 00:30:34,065
that's something I'd welcome.

850
00:30:35,633 --> 00:30:37,735
But since President Wang asked,

851
00:30:38,703 --> 00:30:40,271
we can't afford to offend the leadership.

852
00:30:42,674 --> 00:30:43,708
Let's move you to another region.

853
00:30:47,478 --> 00:30:48,713
What region

854
00:30:49,013 --> 00:30:50,014
can you even move me to?

855
00:30:53,852 --> 00:30:54,719
Fushan Hospital.

856
00:30:55,086 --> 00:30:55,987
They've opened a branch

857
00:30:56,054 --> 00:30:56,888
in Dongjiang's suburbs.

858
00:30:57,188 --> 00:30:57,989
They invested heavily.

859
00:30:58,990 --> 00:31:00,325
It's far away,

860
00:31:00,992 --> 00:31:01,826
but it's backed

861
00:31:01,893 --> 00:31:03,328
by a major tertiary hospital.

862
00:31:03,928 --> 00:31:04,963
The market potential

863
00:31:04,996 --> 00:31:05,930
is enormous.

864
00:31:06,664 --> 00:31:07,465
And you can also work

865
00:31:07,665 --> 00:31:08,366
the Kuncheng Hospital account.

866
00:31:08,433 --> 00:31:09,834
You can make some rounds there.

867
00:31:12,103 --> 00:31:13,805
So I'm the one who expands new territory?

868
00:31:14,305 --> 00:31:15,440
I go out hunting,

869
00:31:15,473 --> 00:31:16,574
bring the meat back for everyone,

870
00:31:16,808 --> 00:31:17,609
and in the end,

871
00:31:17,742 --> 00:31:19,110
I'm left gnawing the bones.

872
00:31:20,111 --> 00:31:20,745
Look at you.

873
00:31:22,513 --> 00:31:24,415
That mouth never gives anyone a break.

874
00:31:25,516 --> 00:31:26,517
I won't shortchange you.

875
00:31:28,486 --> 00:31:29,187
We can renegotiate

876
00:31:29,287 --> 00:31:30,455
the weighting of your performance bonus.

877
00:31:30,755 --> 00:31:32,123
I'll raise it substantially.

878
00:31:32,957 --> 00:31:34,525
Whatever other support you want,

879
00:31:34,559 --> 00:31:35,326
just ask.

880
00:31:35,960 --> 00:31:36,961
Just don't leave me caught

881
00:31:36,995 --> 00:31:38,396
between you and the client.

882
00:31:38,796 --> 00:31:39,631
I only hope

883
00:31:40,398 --> 00:31:41,966
you can understand my difficulties.

884
00:31:48,206 --> 00:31:49,040
This is wonderful.

885
00:31:49,574 --> 00:31:50,375
With you involved,

886
00:31:50,441 --> 00:31:52,110
little Doudou has real hope.

887
00:31:53,611 --> 00:31:54,913
I also looked into it.

888
00:31:55,213 --> 00:31:56,047
For a 3.5-millimeter

889
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:57,448
PDA in an extremely low-birth-weight premature infant,

890
00:31:57,448 --> 00:31:58,449
transcatheter closure

891
00:31:58,583 --> 00:32:00,118
there are very few

892
00:32:00,118 --> 00:32:01,920
international guidelines available.

893
00:32:03,354 --> 00:32:04,322
For this intervention,

894
00:32:04,789 --> 00:32:06,991
there really is no suitable occluder.

895
00:32:07,825 --> 00:32:09,127
But a fourth-generation vascular plug

896
00:32:09,127 --> 00:32:09,894
can be used instead.

897
00:32:10,795 --> 00:32:11,930
I've already done three cases.

898
00:32:12,797 --> 00:32:14,332
None was

899
00:32:14,332 --> 00:32:16,467
as extreme as little Doudou's,

900
00:32:16,634 --> 00:32:17,235
But if we

901
00:32:17,268 --> 00:32:18,603
complete a few more cases,

902
00:32:19,237 --> 00:32:20,838
we can provide more

903
00:32:20,872 --> 00:32:21,706
evidence-based support,

904
00:32:21,973 --> 00:32:22,974
and also put forward

905
00:32:23,007 --> 00:32:25,710
Chinese experts' views and recommendations.

906
00:32:26,311 --> 00:32:26,711
Yes.

907
00:32:27,245 --> 00:32:28,546
We absolutely can't let foreigners

908
00:32:28,613 --> 00:32:29,113
have the final say on everything.

909
00:32:30,848 --> 00:32:31,849
You'll scrub in too, right?

910
00:32:32,317 --> 00:32:32,750
Of course.

911
00:32:32,951 --> 00:32:33,951
I've already applied

912
00:32:34,085 --> 00:32:35,486
to attend with the manufacturer's technician.

913
00:32:36,354 --> 00:32:36,954
Thank you for your help.

914
00:32:37,188 --> 00:32:38,256
I heard

915
00:32:38,957 --> 00:32:41,125
that last time the mother had an emergency

916
00:32:41,492 --> 00:32:42,327
with fetal hypoxia,

917
00:32:42,527 --> 00:32:43,728
and you handled it urgently too.

918
00:32:44,495 --> 00:32:44,962
Yes.

919
00:32:45,930 --> 00:32:47,332
Hongxia was terrified that day.

920
00:32:47,465 --> 00:32:48,266
As a mother,

921
00:32:48,399 --> 00:32:50,034
I understand how she felt.

922
00:32:53,771 --> 00:32:54,505
Professor Fang,

923
00:32:54,572 --> 00:32:56,107
you know I have a child, right?

924
00:32:59,944 --> 00:33:00,678
Is he doing okay?

925
00:33:01,612 --> 00:33:02,613
At present, it hasn't affected

926
00:33:02,613 --> 00:33:03,247
his normal life.

927
00:33:03,448 --> 00:33:04,349
He's already in elementary school.

928
00:33:04,949 --> 00:33:06,884
Regular follow-up is enough.

929
00:33:08,086 --> 00:33:08,920
Thank you.

930
00:33:09,354 --> 00:33:10,254
It was nothing.

931
00:33:13,491 --> 00:33:14,525
Ever since I learned

932
00:33:14,692 --> 00:33:16,027
that little Senlin was ill,

933
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:17,795
all I wanted was to earn money,

934
00:33:18,262 --> 00:33:19,230
spend more time with him,

935
00:33:19,464 --> 00:33:20,064
and raise him well.

936
00:33:20,531 --> 00:33:21,766
I hoped he could grow up safely.

937
00:33:22,367 --> 00:33:24,135
Later, when I met Xiaofeng again,

938
00:33:25,570 --> 00:33:27,005
at first, I didn't have

939
00:33:27,038 --> 00:33:28,072
any other thoughts.

940
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:29,807
Later...

941
00:33:31,676 --> 00:33:33,044
I never expected things to turn out this way.

942
00:33:34,011 --> 00:33:34,645
It must be fate.

943
00:33:35,046 --> 00:33:35,613
That's good.

944
00:33:36,314 --> 00:33:36,714
Yes.

945
00:33:37,915 --> 00:33:38,750
But don't worry.

946
00:33:39,183 --> 00:33:40,051
As for little Senlin,

947
00:33:40,184 --> 00:33:41,452
I've already made plans for him.

948
00:33:41,853 --> 00:33:43,154
He will never become a burden to Xiaofeng.

949
00:33:44,155 --> 00:33:45,590
There's no question of burden.

950
00:33:46,557 --> 00:33:47,925
Xiaofeng has always known his own mind.

951
00:33:48,426 --> 00:33:50,194
If he chose to be with you,

952
00:33:50,561 --> 00:33:51,763
he must have thought it through.

953
00:33:52,563 --> 00:33:52,964
As for me,

954
00:33:53,030 --> 00:33:54,165
you have even less reason to worry.

955
00:33:54,365 --> 00:33:55,233
I understand everything.

956
00:33:57,969 --> 00:33:58,636
Thank you.

957
00:33:59,203 --> 00:34:00,238
Thank you for understanding.

958
00:34:02,440 --> 00:34:03,241
When the procedure is scheduled,

959
00:34:03,241 --> 00:34:04,042
I'll let you know.

960
00:34:04,709 --> 00:34:05,676
The product is readily available, right?

961
00:34:06,110 --> 00:34:06,477
Yes.

962
00:34:06,711 --> 00:34:07,612
I've already prepared it.

963
00:34:11,749 --> 00:34:13,384
The baby's overall condition

964
00:34:13,451 --> 00:34:14,585
has remained relatively stable,

965
00:34:15,720 --> 00:34:16,954
and there are no other

966
00:34:17,054 --> 00:34:18,623
cardiac malformations.

967
00:34:18,890 --> 00:34:20,191
The femoral artery and vein

968
00:34:20,358 --> 00:34:21,692
are both normal.

969
00:34:21,793 --> 00:34:22,760
So I think

970
00:34:22,794 --> 00:34:23,795
the puncture

971
00:34:24,095 --> 00:34:25,163
has a high chance of success.

972
00:34:26,597 --> 00:34:28,132
Based on the overall assessment,

973
00:34:28,332 --> 00:34:28,966
I believe

974
00:34:29,033 --> 00:34:29,967
transcatheter PDA closure

975
00:34:30,401 --> 00:34:31,436
is worth attempting.

976
00:34:32,437 --> 00:34:33,671
Looking at it this way,

977
00:34:33,905 --> 00:34:35,239
the baby is still fairly fortunate.

978
00:34:36,174 --> 00:34:37,875
I hope he gets through this.

979
00:34:39,043 --> 00:34:40,678
But for an

980
00:34:40,878 --> 00:34:42,647
extremely low-birth-weight premature infant like this,

981
00:34:42,847 --> 00:34:45,450
even the trip

982
00:34:45,550 --> 00:34:46,951
from the NICU to the cath lab

983
00:34:46,984 --> 00:34:47,919
is dangerous.

984
00:34:48,519 --> 00:34:50,888
If hypothermia occurs,

985
00:34:51,122 --> 00:34:52,523
a whole series of complications

986
00:34:52,690 --> 00:34:53,991
could follow.

987
00:34:54,325 --> 00:34:55,326
Leave that to us.

988
00:34:55,793 --> 00:34:56,894
Neonatology

989
00:34:57,028 --> 00:34:58,162
and Anesthesiology

990
00:34:58,563 --> 00:35:00,465
will ensure safe transport.

991
00:35:01,666 --> 00:35:02,733
As for the operating table,

992
00:35:02,767 --> 00:35:04,001
we'll use a warming blanket

993
00:35:04,068 --> 00:35:05,436
and preheat it to above 37 degrees Celsius.

994
00:35:06,904 --> 00:35:07,805
For the surgical team,

995
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:09,106
I can assemble

996
00:35:09,173 --> 00:35:10,475
top specialists from every department

997
00:35:10,808 --> 00:35:11,642
across the hospital.

998
00:35:12,243 --> 00:35:13,077
But no matter what,

999
00:35:13,244 --> 00:35:14,312
we must ensure

1000
00:35:14,345 --> 00:35:15,413
the procedure is safe and successful.

1001
00:35:17,482 --> 00:35:18,316
If you need

1002
00:35:18,349 --> 00:35:19,050
anything else,

1003
00:35:19,283 --> 00:35:20,852
just let me know.

1004
00:35:21,185 --> 00:35:21,919
Thank you, President Wang.

1005
00:35:36,234 --> 00:35:37,635
A true master is still a master.

1006
00:35:38,169 --> 00:35:38,603
It hasn't been that long,

1007
00:35:38,603 --> 00:35:39,237
The C-arm

1008
00:35:39,570 --> 00:35:40,671
doesn't faze her at all.

1009
00:35:41,839 --> 00:35:43,174
So bold, Professor Fang.

1010
00:35:45,276 --> 00:35:46,611
I never thought in my lifetime

1011
00:35:46,844 --> 00:35:47,745
I'd see Professor Fang

1012
00:35:47,845 --> 00:35:49,347
and Director Zhou operating together.

1013
00:35:56,687 --> 00:35:58,322
My God, a baby this small...

1014
00:35:58,523 --> 00:35:59,290
His heart

1015
00:35:59,323 --> 00:36:00,291
must be about the size

1016
00:36:00,291 --> 00:36:00,758
of a little quail egg.

1017
00:36:01,626 --> 00:36:02,560
The femoral vein may be

1018
00:36:02,560 --> 00:36:03,394
only about two millimeters.

1019
00:36:03,761 --> 00:36:05,062
Operating under these conditions

1020
00:36:05,229 --> 00:36:06,664
is truly pushing the limits.

1021
00:36:07,732 --> 00:36:09,567
It's like placing a raw quail egg

1022
00:36:09,634 --> 00:36:10,768
inside a straw cup,

1023
00:36:11,469 --> 00:36:12,703
then using only a guidewire

1024
00:36:12,803 --> 00:36:14,205
to pass through a winding straw

1025
00:36:14,272 --> 00:36:15,406
thinner than a toothpick,

1026
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:16,707
pierce the shell,

1027
00:36:16,807 --> 00:36:17,975
and deliver a plug inside

1028
00:36:18,109 --> 00:36:19,944
to close a hole in the yolk membrane,

1029
00:36:20,278 --> 00:36:21,412
without damaging the egg

1030
00:36:21,546 --> 00:36:22,713
or the straw.

1031
00:36:22,914 --> 00:36:23,548
And remember,

1032
00:36:23,814 --> 00:36:25,149
the heart is still beating the whole time.

1033
00:36:37,828 --> 00:36:38,729
C-arm, left lateral view.

1034
00:36:51,809 --> 00:36:52,643
Let's take a measurement.

1035
00:37:01,118 --> 00:37:02,386
Just as we predicted.

1036
00:37:03,387 --> 00:37:04,789
Use a six-millimeter vascular plug.

1037
00:38:11,922 --> 00:38:12,923
The occluder is in position.

1038
00:38:13,591 --> 00:38:14,225
Director Liao,

1039
00:38:14,525 --> 00:38:15,526
check with ultrasound.

1040
00:38:27,438 --> 00:38:28,506
No residual shunt.

1041
00:38:29,073 --> 00:38:30,641
No obstruction of flow

1042
00:38:30,808 --> 00:38:32,076
in the left pulmonary artery or descending aorta.

1043
00:38:36,113 --> 00:38:36,914
There's a tiny amount of flow

1044
00:38:36,914 --> 00:38:38,349
through the vascular plug.

1045
00:38:38,482 --> 00:38:39,483
That's not a problem.

1046
00:38:40,851 --> 00:38:42,586
The key is stability.

1047
00:38:42,953 --> 00:38:45,156
We need to perform a push-pull test.

1048
00:38:56,167 --> 00:38:57,068
No displacement.

1049
00:38:58,269 --> 00:38:58,936
Xiaofeng, look.

1050
00:38:59,670 --> 00:39:00,371
The vascular plug

1051
00:39:00,404 --> 00:39:01,472
is slightly deformed

1052
00:39:02,006 --> 00:39:03,307
inside the ductus arteriosus.

1053
00:39:06,344 --> 00:39:07,345
What does that mean?

1054
00:39:07,611 --> 00:39:09,013
Slight deformation of the vascular plug

1055
00:39:09,246 --> 00:39:11,015
means it's seated

1056
00:39:11,115 --> 00:39:12,650
with just the right amount of compression.

1057
00:39:12,950 --> 00:39:14,118
The size is appropriate too.

1058
00:39:14,351 --> 00:39:15,453
That makes migration unlikely.

1059
00:39:20,424 --> 00:39:21,158
We can release it.

1060
00:39:31,268 --> 00:39:32,236
Director Liao, check again.

1061
00:39:54,425 --> 00:39:55,192
No displacement.

1062
00:39:57,161 --> 00:39:58,629
The residual leak is decreasing too.

1063
00:40:00,598 --> 00:40:01,632
We did it.

1064
00:40:43,073 --> 00:40:44,442
The weather is really nice today.

1065
00:40:46,010 --> 00:40:46,877
We pulled off something huge.

1066
00:40:47,044 --> 00:40:47,878
I feel completely refreshed.

1067
00:40:49,513 --> 00:40:50,481
Do you still have to go back to the company?

1068
00:40:50,748 --> 00:40:51,482
Or do you want to come to my office

1069
00:40:51,549 --> 00:40:52,283
for a cup of coffee?

1070
00:40:53,250 --> 00:40:54,685
No coffee.

1071
00:40:56,854 --> 00:40:57,688
Are you free tonight?

1072
00:40:58,122 --> 00:40:58,856
Let's have dinner.

1073
00:40:59,723 --> 00:41:00,524
There's something I need to tell you.

1074
00:41:01,992 --> 00:41:03,227
What is it? Why the mystery?

1075
00:41:13,237 --> 00:41:13,871
I'm being transferred.

1076
00:41:15,172 --> 00:41:15,840
Where?

1077
00:41:18,609 --> 00:41:19,677
Fushan Hospital.

1078
00:41:19,844 --> 00:41:21,745
They opened a new branch in the suburbs.

1079
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:24,048
It's fairly large.

1080
00:41:24,715 --> 00:41:26,483
And I was also given

1081
00:41:26,684 --> 00:41:27,751
the entire Kunshan region.

1082
00:41:28,319 --> 00:41:29,653
Those areas are so remote.

1083
00:41:29,954 --> 00:41:31,121
Qin Xiong has gone too far.

1084
00:41:32,189 --> 00:41:33,557
He didn't force me.

1085
00:41:33,691 --> 00:41:34,692
I agreed to it.

1086
00:41:35,125 --> 00:41:36,227
Why would you do that?

1087
00:41:37,094 --> 00:41:38,095
Didn't we already agree?

1088
00:41:38,162 --> 00:41:38,896
I said I would handle it.

1089
00:41:38,963 --> 00:41:39,663
You didn't need to move.

1090
00:41:44,802 --> 00:41:46,303
This isn't only

1091
00:41:46,303 --> 00:41:47,104
because of you.

1092
00:41:48,372 --> 00:41:49,173
President Qin

1093
00:41:49,373 --> 00:41:50,307
helped secure funding

1094
00:41:50,307 --> 00:41:51,575
for little Doudou.

1095
00:41:51,675 --> 00:41:52,743
He kept his promise.

1096
00:41:52,877 --> 00:41:54,111
So I'm keeping mine.

1097
00:41:54,278 --> 00:41:54,912
I switch regions.

1098
00:41:55,312 --> 00:41:56,647
Everyone gets what they want.

1099
00:41:59,884 --> 00:42:00,951
But this is unfair to you.

1100
00:42:03,787 --> 00:42:04,889
Do you remember

1101
00:42:05,022 --> 00:42:05,956
what I told you

1102
00:42:06,023 --> 00:42:06,891
when I was in college?

1103
00:42:07,491 --> 00:42:08,525
I said that in middle school,

1104
00:42:08,592 --> 00:42:09,760
I had already decided

1105
00:42:10,227 --> 00:42:11,595
I would get into medical school.

1106
00:42:13,430 --> 00:42:15,032
Integrated bachelor's, master's, and doctoral training,

1107
00:42:15,633 --> 00:42:16,367
internship,

1108
00:42:16,467 --> 00:42:17,601
residency, specialty training,

1109
00:42:18,035 --> 00:42:18,936
and then clinical practice...

1110
00:42:19,303 --> 00:42:20,104
It was exhausting.

1111
00:42:20,504 --> 00:42:22,206
But I never shed a single tear.

1112
00:42:24,708 --> 00:42:25,643
Last year,

1113
00:42:26,610 --> 00:42:27,311
on the day I was about to leave

1114
00:42:27,411 --> 00:42:28,812
clinical medicine,

1115
00:42:29,480 --> 00:42:30,247
I cried alone

1116
00:42:30,281 --> 00:42:31,515
the entire night.

1117
00:42:33,851 --> 00:42:34,652
The excitement I felt

1118
00:42:34,685 --> 00:42:35,920
when I received my medical school admission letter

1119
00:42:35,986 --> 00:42:36,987
was immense.

1120
00:42:37,388 --> 00:42:38,989
And when I took off my white coat,

1121
00:42:39,557 --> 00:42:40,424
the pain was just as great.

1122
00:42:41,592 --> 00:42:43,494
More than a decade of dreams and hard work

1123
00:42:44,128 --> 00:42:45,396
abandoned in a single day.

1124
00:42:46,964 --> 00:42:47,598
That feeling...

1125
00:42:47,631 --> 00:42:48,732
you must understand it.

1126
00:42:50,167 --> 00:42:50,968
So

1127
00:42:51,769 --> 00:42:53,003
I don't want you

1128
00:42:53,804 --> 00:42:56,040
to feel the same regret I did.
